Defendant Janine A Brunia in court with Attorney Katie B. Bricco.  Lindsey Hirt appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a no contest plea to Count #1.  Court performs plea colloquy and finds Defendant guilty of Count #1.  State gives sentencing recommendations.  Beth J., daughter of victim, makes statements.  Attorney Bricco makes statements regarding sentencing.  Defendant makes statements. Court sentences the Defendant to the following:

COUNT #1:  WITHHELD SENTENCE

TERM OF PROBATION:  2 YEARS

CONDITIONS OF PROBATON:  
____Follow through with any assessments/treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
____Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling 
____No contact with: victim or his family members or place where crime was committed 
____DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done 

COSTS:  $278.00 & $250.00 DNA surcharge (to be paid as a condition of probation)

CONDITION TIME:  30 Days, Non-working hours with standard release conditions - STAYED - to be used at agent's discretion
